means: （时间）消逝，过去( elapse的现在分词 )

sentence.Network_en: Along with the elapsing of year, this book will be more precious.
sentence.Network_cn: 随着年代的流逝, 这本书将越发珍贵.

sentence.Network_en: With time elapsing, the flaps collapse up on his clapper's lap.
sentence.Network_cn: 随着时间流逝, 袋盖在拍手者的膝上堆叠起来.

sentence.Network_en: These things happen quickly on - screen, with the years elapsing in a heartbeat.
sentence.Network_cn: 种种因果在银幕上飞快掠过, 而一年年的岁月以心跳的速度流逝着.
